text:
@SueMentors Oh, I didn't build one - in fact I worked on one with BUSPH COVID Corps that didn't release because of all the caveats.

Prof. Oster did release a risk comparison tool in a google sheet though (as best I remember) which is where I take issue with the statement.
@alexjgoldstein @FacesOfCOVID Thank you for reminding folks to respect the space of the grieving families.

Exponential growth I'm happy to celebrate: @NeoliberalSnow climbing to more than 10K followers in a matter of weeks.

Thanks for being the public health humor account that we need as we head into pandemic year three. https://t.co/J4WXvN0jK8

Losing a child is a life altering trauma where an unlikely outcome happens to you.

The pandemic narrative is that *most kids* who get COVID will be fine. But some won't.

The disregard for those families hurts so acutely when I see it on my feed, thinking about our loss. 1/2 https://t.co/qpvjpkHQmI

@SueMentors And just to be clear (since I realize this may be reinterpreted) - my dad is a transplant patient living his best life at home (joy of home-based hobbies). I don't want him to make it through that surgery only to have this new 'let COVID rip!' mentality hit that household.
